The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Family held for Bengal murder

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Aug. 9: A 56-year- old state government employee was today found dead in his Sonarpur home, and his family has been taken in for questioning. 

 Dilip Dass wife Santana, 49, daughter Manasi, 23, and son Manas, 19, were detained by police who said their relations with the dead man were strained because he would allegedly borrow money from friends for gambling.

 The police arrived at Dass rented flat in Bhattacharyapara around 11am following a call from neighbours. We saw Das lying dead on his bed with some bruises on his left elbow and left knee, said an officer of Sonarpur police station. 

 An officer said Das had allegedly borrowed about Rs 5 lakh from different people for gambling. His family was unhappy about moneylenders frequenting their house. 




